","header":"She died April 1866","body":"Fanny Pixley married James Sperry in Great Barrington in January 1812 and they lived at Henrietta, New York, raising eight children across three decades; she died April 29, 1866 in Rochester at approximately seventy-eight, and James outlived her by almost exactly eleven months — dying March 29, 1867 also in Rochester. The Pixley genealogy corrects the EH date: Fanny died in 1866, not 1867 — she went first, after fifty-four years of marriage, and James followed in the same city the following spring."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Edward Hooker, Descendants of Rev. Thomas Hooker (1909)","url":"https://archive.org/details/descendantsofrev00hook"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"fanny-sperry-1788"},"H02397":{"id":"H02397","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Sarah","middle_name":"Ann","last_name":"Latting","maiden_name":"Sperry","married_names":["Latting"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Sarah Ann Latting"},"birth":{"year":1812,"month":10,"city":"East Bloomfield","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1896,"month":3,"country":"United States"},"residence":{"country":"United States"},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":true,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":8,"generation_from_john_talcott":7,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"I00989","mother_id":"H01264"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I01004","location_country":"United States","children_ids":["H03834a","H03835","H03836"]}],"education":[],"career":[{"role":"Teacher","organization":"Henrietta Academy, Henrietta, New York","notes":"EH: 'she a teacher in his school' — taught at Henrietta Academy where her husband William Waring Latting was principal. Later moved to Rochester NY."}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["educator"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"She taught in the school her husband ran","body":"Sarah Ann Sperry married William Waring Latting of Baltimore, Maryland, who was principal of Henrietta Academy in Monroe County, New York — and she became a teacher in his school, one of the few documented instances in this tree where a wife's professional role was specifically recorded in the genealogical source rather than erased by it. The couple eventually moved to Rochester, where she died in March 1896, having outlived a son James Sperry Latting and having named her daughter Minnie Elizabeth for the Sperry family that her Pixley mother carried into the marriage."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Edward Hooker, Descendants of Rev. Thomas Hooker (1909)","url":"https://archive.org/details/descendantsofrev00hook"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"sarah-latting-1812"},"I01004":{"id":"I01004","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"William","middle_name":"Waring","last_name":"Latting","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"William Waring Latting"},"birth":{},"baptism":{},"death":{},"residence":{"country":"United States"},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H02397","location_country":"United States","children_ids":["H03834a","H038